  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Celiac disease is an autoimmune process that causes destructive changes in the epithel of the
      small bowel and it is also a pre-malignant state (e.g lymphoma). The aim of the study is to
      examine telomere length and other parameters of genetic instability from peripheral blood
      lymphocytes of patients with celiac disease compared with healthy controls.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
